## Python Implementation\
\
```python\
def kindness(time_seconds: float, darkness: float) -> float:\
    """\
    Calculates Kindness using the formula: K = T / D\
\
    Args:\
        time_seconds: Time spent holding the light\
        darkness: Magnitude of darkness faced (must be > 0)\
\
    Returns:\
        Kindness value (float)\
\
    Raises:\
        ValueError if darkness <= 0\
    """\
    if darkness <= 0:\
        raise ValueError("Darkness must be greater than zero. No kindness can emerge from a vacuum.")\
\
    return time_seconds / darkness\
```\
